---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Presentation from "../../../components/Presentation.astro";
import Divider from "../../../components/ui/Divider.astro";
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ListItem from "../../../components/ui/ListItem.astro";

import WarningSign from "../../../assets/courses/get-the-edge/img/warning-sign.svg";
import CPUImg from "../../../assets/courses/get-the-edge/img/cpu.png";
import MotherboardImg from "../../../assets/courses/get-the-edge/img/motherboard.png";
import IntelAMDImg from "../../../assets/courses/get-the-edge/img/intel-amd.png";
import CPUCoolerImg from "../../../assets/courses/get-the-edge/img/cpu-cooler.png";
---

<Layout>
  <div class="container my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-10">
        <a
          href="/courses/get-the-edge/"
          class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-light mb-3"
        >
          <i class="si-arrow-left"></i> Back
        </a>

        <h1>Session 02: Introduction</h1>
        <Divider variant="8" classes="mb-5" />

        <!-- Launch / Concept -->
        <section id="launch">
          <Presentation>
            <section>
              <h2>Session 02</h2>
              <h3 class="text-sn-theme">CPUs and Motherboards</h3>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Agenda</h2>
              <ul>
                <ListItem>Introduce CPUs</ListItem>
                <ListItem className="fragment">Introduce Motherboards</ListItem>
                <ListItem className="fragment">Install a CPU</ListItem>
                <ListItem className="fragment">Introduce CPU Coolers</ListItem>
                <ListItem className="fragment">Install a CPU Cooler</ListItem>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>The CPU</h2>

              <div class="container-fluid">
                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <p>
                      A CPU (Central Processing Unit) is the brain of the
                      computer, responsible for executing instructions and
                      processing data.
                    </p>
                    <p class="fragment">
                      Processors are made up of billions of components called
                      transistors, which act as tiny switches that help process
                      and execute instructions.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <img src={CPUImg.src} alt="CPU" class="img-fluid" />
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>CPU Characteristics</h2>
              <ul>
                <ListItem>Clock Speed (measured in GHz)</ListItem>
                <ListItem className="fragment">Number of Cores</ListItem>
                <ListItem className="fragment">Generation (or version)</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment">Cache</ListItem>
              </ul>
              <p class="fragment">
                <strong>Note:</strong> CPUs can execute billions of instructions per
                second!
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Intel and AMD Brands</h2>
              <div class="container-fluid">
                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <p>
                      There are two major CPU brands to choose from: <strong
                        >AMD</strong
                      > and <strong>Intel</strong>.
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                      <ListItem className="fragment"
                        >They are fierce rivals, but both make incredible
                        processors.</ListItem
                      >
                      <ListItem className="fragment"
                        ><strong>The Golden Rule:</strong> They are NOT interchangeable.
                        An Intel CPU requires an Intel motherboard, and an AMD CPU
                        requires an AMD motherboard.</ListItem
                      >
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <img
                      src={IntelAMDImg.src}
                      alt="Intel AMD"
                      class="img-fluid"
                    />
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>PGA vs. LGA Sockets</h2>
              <p>
                How the CPU connects to the motherboard depends on the brand and
                generation:
              </p>
              <ul>
                <ListItem
                  ><strong>LGA (Land Grid Array):</strong> The delicate pins are on
                  the <em>motherboard socket</em>. The bottom of the CPU is
                  flat. (Used by all modern Intel and AMD AM5 CPUs).</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  ><strong>PGA (Pin Grid Array):</strong> The delicate pins are directly
                  on the <em>bottom of the CPU</em>. (Used by older AMD AM4
                  CPUs).</ListItem
                >
              </ul>
              <p class="fragment text-sn-theme">
                🚨 NEVER touch the pins on a motherboard socket or a PGA CPU! 🚨
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>The Motherboard</h2>
              <div class="container-fluid">
                <div class="row align-items-center">
                  <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <p>
                      A motherboard is the main circuit board of a computer,
                      connecting all components like the CPU, RAM, and storage
                      so they can work together.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                    <img
                      src={MotherboardImg.src}
                      alt="Motherboard"
                      class="img-fluid"
                    />
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Motherboard Characteristics</h2>
              <ul>
                <ListItem
                  ><strong>Chipset</strong> - Determines compatibility with processors,
                  RAM, and storage devices.</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  ><strong>CPU Socket</strong> - The connector that houses the processor.</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  ><strong>RAM Slots</strong> - Provides space for memory modules.</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  ><strong>Expansion Slots</strong> - Includes PCIe slots for graphics
                  cards, sound cards, and other upgrades.</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  ><strong>Power Connectors</strong> - Delivers power from the PSU
                  to the board.</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  ><strong>Storage Connectors</strong> - Supports SSDs, HDDs, and
                  M.2 drives.</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  ><strong>USB & Connectivity Ports</strong></ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  ><strong>Form Factor</strong> - Defines the size and shape.</ListItem
                >
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Installing a CPU</h2>

              <div class="border border-primary mt-3 p-3">
                <Image
                  src={WarningSign}
                  alt="warning sign"
                  class="slow-flash"
                  width={128}
                />
                <p>
                  This is one of the most delicate tasks of assembling a
                  computer! Listen carefully to the installation instructions.
                </p>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>How to Install a CPU</h2>
              <ol>
                <ListItem>Open the socket</ListItem>
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  >Align the CPU to the correct position (look for the
                  triangles)</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  >Gently seat the CPU into the socket</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  >Lock the CPU in the socket</ListItem
                >
              </ol>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Hands-On Task</h2>
              <p>
                Practice installing a CPU into an LGA socket and an older PGA
                socket.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>CPU Cooling</h2>
              <p>CPUs run very hot!</p>
              <p class="fragment">
                Without a cooling fan, a CPU can overheat within seconds to
                minutes under heavy load.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <section>
                <h2>CPU Coolers (Air)</h2>

                <div class="container-fluid">
                  <div class="row align-items-center">
                    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                      <ul>
                        <ListItem
                          ><strong>Heatsinks:</strong> Draw heat away from the CPU.</ListItem
                        >
                        <ListItem className="fragment"
                          ><strong>Fans:</strong> Push cool air through the heatsink
                          to cool it down.</ListItem
                        >
                      </ul>
                      <p class="fragment">
                        ⬇️ <em>Press down for Water Cooling info</em>
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6">
                      <img
                      src={CPUCoolerImg.src}
                      alt="CPU Cooler"
                      class="img-fluid"
                    />
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </section>

              <section>
                <h2>Water Cooling</h2>
                <p>
                  Uses a radiator, fluid, a pump, and a metal block to cool the
                  CPU.
                </p>
                <ul>
                  <ListItem>Better cooling performance</ListItem>
                  <ListItem className="fragment">Requires maintenance</ListItem>
                  <ListItem className="fragment"
                    >Slightly more difficult assembly</ListItem
                  >
                </ul>
              </section>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Installing a CPU Cooler</h2>
              <ol>
                <ListItem
                  >Apply fresh thermal paste in a small, pea-sized amount at the
                  center of the CPU <em>(Skip for GTE Camp Stations)</em
                  ></ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  >Align the new fan and heatsink with the mounting holes on the
                  motherboard</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  >Secure the heatsink by pressing down or screwing it in place,
                  ensuring even pressure</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem className="fragment"
                  >Connect the fan cable to the CPU fan header on the
                  motherboard</ListItem
                >
              </ol>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Cooler Challenge!</h2>
              <p>Try installing a cooler other than the one at your station.</p>
            </section>
          </Presentation>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
